 Asia. Many soldiers were Orthodox Ostjuden, and over 130 Feldrabbiner (chaplains) served among them. Antisemitism was present but generally not overt. The book uses personal diaries and newspaper articles (most available in English for the first time) to describe their stories, and compares the experiences of Jews in German, Russian, and Italian armies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2022) 0aJewish soldierszAustriaxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewish soldierszAustriaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszAustriaxHistoryy19th century. 0aJewszAustriaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMilitary chaplainszAustriaxHistoryy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xChaplains. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918zAustria. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Austria & Hungary.2bisacsh  aAustro-Hungary.  aBalkans.  aEastern Europe.  aFeldrabbiner.  aItaly.  aJudaism.  aOrthodox soldiers.  aPOWs.  aPrisoners of War.  aRussia.  aSiberia.  aTurkestan.  aantisemitism.  aarchival materials.  achaplains.  acorrespondence.  ahistory.  ajournals.  areligion.  awar.1 aLamprecht, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRauchensteiner, Manfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076741408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644696910zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644696910423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644696910/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076741-4  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aE